$interpreted: Guesthouse Boss: This tonic is called the Tonic of Rebirth. It can keep you virile and beautiful. This tonic helped birth many of the past greats on Hot Spring Street.
Guesthouse Boss: That said, there is a price for greatness... can you pay that price, Beyata?
Beyata: For my grandfather, and for you... yes, I can!
Beyata: Gyaagh!!
Guesthouse Boss: You must grin and bear it as the tonic cleanses your dirty feathers and replaces them with divine beauty!
Beyata: It hurts!! Yeagh, mngh, ungh, somebody help me, please!
Guesthouse Boss: ...Do not worry, this will pass. You have to fight it!
Guesthouse Boss: Fight it and become Hot Spring Street's most radiant flower!
Beyata: Yaaaaaaaaagh!!
Beyata: B-Boss? Did I do a good job?
Beyata: Really? Thank you, I'm so happy.
Beyata: ...Grandfather? You're here, too?
Beyata: Are you here to pat my head, like before?
Beyata: Hehe, your hands are so warm... I feel so safe...
: Three months later, on mail day.
Sighing Girl: Beyata has really changed over these past few months. She's so confident and beautiful... no wonder all the customers want her.
Gossiping Girl: She's so busy and yet she's always so pretty, never looks tired at all... how does she do it?
Cruel Staff: Hey, keep it down!
Guesthouse Boss: ...Now, the rules of my guesthouse are very simple. Take more customers, get better treatment, make more money.
Guesthouse Boss: If you're not doing it for yourself, then at least work hard for your families back home.
Guesthouse Boss: Now, let's see whose been our most popular girl this month... Ah, it's Beyata, just like last month. Come up and get your mail, Beyata.
Beyata: Ah, yes...
Sighing Girl: Jeez, most popular for two months in a row...
Guesthouse Boss: ...Next is─
Beyata: "I've been improving, I'm even out of bed and walking a bit now..."
Beyata: Ever since that day, things have really been looking up...
Gossiping Girl: Huh? What's that supposed to mean?
Gossiping Girl: What do you mean "that day"? What happened!? Did you learn some kind of special technique or something?
Beyata: Ah, don't be silly, I have no "special techniques". I just listen to the boss, and everything works out...
Panicked Staff: ─Boss, we've got a problem!
Panicked Staff: This morning, Lily was bathing in the tonic, and then... she drowned!
Guesthouse Boss: What are you so panicked about? People die, that's how it goes... Now, I'm busy handing out mail. You go deal with this first.
Gossiping Girl: What, she drowned!? And she was just starting to really make something of herself... Beyata, are you crying? You must have been good friends...
Beyata: ...How could Lily just go and die like that!? Does she not realize how much extra work that'll give the Boss!?
Gossiping Girl: ....Eh?
Guesthouse Boss: Alright, ladies, mail time is over. You can all head back.
Guesthouse Boss: Oh, Beyata... you stay behind.
Guesthouse Boss: It seems that Lily wasn't up to the tonic's challenge... too bad, she was a strong one.
Beyata: I will bring the other girls over to apologize for Lily's actions, for making things harder on you...
Guesthouse Boss: The money wasted on Lily's tonic isn't something a simple "sorry" can repay.
Guesthouse Boss: It seems you are the only true warrior here, Beyata.
Beyata: M-Me? Are you saying... you're not throwing me out?
Guesthouse Boss: Throw you out!? How could I do that, you're our best girl!
Beyata: O-Okay! Then leave it to me! I'll make you proud, Boss!
